A 25-year-old man, Abdulwahab, who was one of the nine victims of a train accident in Kano has died. A family source, Muhammad Bello told newsmen that the deceased who was a tricycle driver died on Monday. He said the victim died at Murtala Muhammad Hospital after suffering from various degrees of injuries as a result of the accident. DAILY POST on Sunday reported that a train travelling from Lagos to Kano crushed a Dangote truck and a tricycle at Obasanjo Road in Kano. The accident injured a least nine persons while the vehicles and properties were damaged. The train rammed into the truck and the tricycle while trying to cross the rail line.